Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees and bring @water{300%ml} to the boil with @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Once the water is boiling, pour in the @bulgur wheat{1/2}, place a lid on the #pot{} and take the pot off the heat for at least ~{25%minutes}, or until the rest of the meal is finished.

> We like to do this at the beginning, as then you don't have to think about it again until the end, and it will stay warm!

In the meantime, cut the @aubergine{1} in half lengthways, cut each half into strips and then chop the strips into roughly 2cm cubes. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into roughly 2cm cubes. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{5%bunch} and @mint{5%bunch}(finely chopped and kept separate).

Put the aubergine and pepper onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle over 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp}, 1/4 tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp} and pop in your oven for ~{30%minutes}.

While your veggies are cooking, tackle the tomatoes! Cut the @vine tomatoes{3} in half through the equator and use a #spoon{} to scoop out the flesh.

> Be careful not to pierce the skin! Don't throw away the tomato flesh!

Crumble the @feta cheese{1} into a #bowl{} and mix together with your chopped parsley. Stuff each tomato with a spoonful of this mixture.

Mix together your @panko breadcrumbs{2} and @hard Italian style cheese{2%tbsp}(grated) and sprinkle this on top of your tomatoes along with a pinch of @?salt{pinch} and a really good grind of @?pepper{pinch}. Drizzle 2 tbsp of oil onto a baking tray, put your tomatoes on the tray and pop in your oven for ~{10%minutes}.

In the meantime, chop up the reserved tomato flesh.

When your bulgur wheat is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and squeeze in the juice of @lemon{1/2} and stir in your veggies, tomato flesh and chopped mint. Taste and add more salt and pepper if necessary.

Serve on plates with your stuffed tomatoes on top and enjoy!